Top remaining workflow gap in the field notes: make all review fixes at once,
then split them into fixup commits for different targets. When one file
carries hunks for two targets the only route today is snapshot / checkout /
re-apply / commit, twice. Wanted:
  git_fixup {target, hunks: [{path, lines: [start, end]}]}
creating the fixup commit from just those working-tree hunks and leaving the
rest of the tree in place. The pieces exist: hunk selection in git_rebase
split, target discovery in git_blame {worktree}. Committing selected worktree
hunks is the missing third.
Magit inspiration: magit-commit-instant-fixup (create the fixup AND fold it
in one move) and magit-commit-absorb / git-absorb (auto-pick the target per
hunk — we have the blame half already); staging by hunk/region is the
underlying primitive.

Done [2026-07-14]: paths / hunks / worktree:true on git_fixup; dangling fixup
commit + byte-snapshot restore + refs/mime-backup/<branch>-worktree parachute;
conflict aborts whole with a target-the-reshaper hint; rehearse previews.
Verified end-to-end through the MCP server on a scratch repo.


