A failed program's partial edits persisting is the interface's biggest
documented footgun (warned about in three places — a sign the default is
wrong). ~rehearse~'s snapshot machinery suggests the engine can support
wrapping every run in an implicit transaction that rolls back on error, with
an opt-out flag (or ~(commit)~-style escape) for programs that want partial
effects. Field notes rated the current default only a "smaller wish", so the
error-text hint task covers the interim.

Done [2026-07-14]: failed dirty run auto-rewinds via the pre-program undo
snapshot; =keep_partial:true= opts out (schema-gated, so rehearse rejects it).
Failure JSON: =rolled_back:true= + dirty:false on rollback; dirty:true only
with keep_partial. Docs updated: instructions preamble, run_program schema,
help {sessions}, docs/mcp-tools.md regenerated. This subsumed the
recovery-hint task: the error text names the recovery in BOTH modes.


