Every editing tool takes BOTH a warm ~session~ id and an auto-opening ~path~;
that overlap is the root of the ~save_buffer {to:}~ footgun and makes
~open_file~ partly redundant with implicit-open. Decide one coherent model
(e.g. ~path~ is sugar resolving to a canonical session; a destination like ~to~
never doubles as the selector) and align every tool + doc to it. Subsumes the
standalone ~save_buffer {to:}~ item.

DONE: the model (~path~/~session~ select the session; ~to~ is the only
destination) was already consistent across tools — the one wart was the
footgun, now fixed: ~save_buffer {to: other}~ writes a copy via
~Workspace::write_copy_to~ and does NOT rebind the session. Resolves the
standalone footgun item below.


