~checkpoint~ / ~list_checkpoints~ / ~restore_checkpoint~ are three tools for a
deliberate-restore-point workflow agents rarely use; automatic ~undo_last~
(every mutation, ring of 8) covers most "oops". Either fold them into one
~checkpoint {action: save|list|restore}~, or keep them but explicitly position
them as advanced with ~undo_last~ as the default net. Net: ~−2 tools of context.

DONE: dropped ~list_checkpoints~; its labels now ride in ~session_status~
(new ~Workspace::checkpoint_labels~). ~checkpoint~/~restore_checkpoint~ kept but
repositioned as advanced (descriptions point at ~undo_last~ + ~session_status~).
Not merged into one ~{action}~ tool — that would force one annotation across
save (append) + restore (destructive), mis-gating like the run_program case.


