Outcome (2026-06-24, branch ~mcp-surface-review~): all five items below done;
surface 29 → 27 tools, no new ones. Cross-file ~grep~ (the "too little") stays
its own TODO.

Verdict (analysis 2026-06-24): the 29-tool surface is coherent at the macro
level — two domains (a buffer you edit; a repo you rewrite) bridged by a shared
conflict surface (~conflicts~ + the ~conflict-*~ lisp verbs serve both a merge
file and a rebase stop; the planned rebase ~edit~/~break~ action deepens the
bridge). The new ~instructions~ index + annotations offset the raw count. The
fat is in Sessions/Editing; the confusion is a few specific seams. Guiding
principle — already shown by the two ~git_rebase~ items above: GROW POWER VIA
PARAMETERS, not new tools; trim the marginal verbs rather than let the count
creep past ~30. Already tracked elsewhere: the cross-file ~grep~ gap (the main
"too little") and the ~save_buffer {to:}~ addressing footgun.


