- State "DONE"       from "TODO"       [2026-06-29 Mo 12:09]
- State "TODO"       from              [2026-06-24 Mi 18:59]
:END:

=reword= / =squash= currently require the entire replacement message as one
string. For a small change (strip a trailing trailer line, fix one paragraph)
the agent must reproduce the whole multi-line message verbatim — verbose and
error-prone.

Accept a message /edit/ instead: e.g. =edits: [{pattern, replacement}]= applied
to the existing message, or directives like delete-trailer / append-line. Should
compose with any sign-off / trailer validation.

DONE (branch =sequencer-tree-edits=): a reword/squash/fixup/edit step can carry
=message_edits= — an ordered list applied to the action's default message, each
either ={find, replace?}= (replace the first literal occurrence; omit replace to
delete; errors if =find= is absent) or ={append}= (add a trailing line). Preserves
the rest of the message, so the =Signed-off-by= a full reword would drop survives.
Reword/edit finds are pre-validated in =begin= before any mutation.


* DONE git_rebase: add an `edit`/`break` step action                    :git:
:PROPERTIES:
:ARCHIVE_TIME: 2026-07-14 Di 15:36
:ARCHIVE_FILE: /vagrant/mime-rs/todo.org
:ARCHIVE_OLPATH: MCP / agent UX
