:END:
:LOGBOOK:
- State "DONE"       from "TODO"       [2026-06-29 Mo 12:09]
- State "TODO"       from              [2026-06-24 Mi 18:59]
:END:

The rebase plan supports only pick/reword/squash/fixup/drop. Add an =edit= (or
=break=) action that pauses the rebase with the target commit checked out, lets
the agent run the normal editing tools (=replace_text= / =run_program=) and the
existing conflict tools against the worktree, then resumes via =git_continue=.

Without it, an agent that needs to amend a commit's tree mid-rebase has to
abandon the in-process sequencer and drive =git rebase -i= + manual continue via
the shell — defeating the point of owning the rebase in-process. Pairs naturally
with the conflict surface already present.

DONE (branch =sequencer-tree-edits=): implemented =edit=. The step applies its
commit then PAUSES with it checked out; =git_continue= folds the worktree changes
into it (an amend), =git_skip= discards the pending edits and resumes, =git_abort=
bails. A conflicted edit step resolves through the existing conflict tools first,
then pauses. Standalone =break= (a no-commit pause) was intentionally OMITTED: an
agent can inspect via =git_status= / =git_show=, and it would force =Step.commit=
to become optional for marginal value.


* DONE Rebase / cherry-pick driver                                      :git:
